{"title":"UAE Tour Women 2024: Route, TV and everything you need to know","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/uae-tour-women-preview","date":1707324400000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/uae-tour-women-preview\">UAE Tour Women 2024: Route, TV and everything you need to know</a></p>\n\n<p>The UAE Tour Women is the second stage race on the WorldTour calendar following the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/2024-pro-cycling-tour-down-under\" target=\"_blank\">Tour Down Under</a>, taking place in the United Arab Emirates from Thursday 8th-Sunday 11th February 2024.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last year’s inaugural edition was won by Lidl-Trek’s Elisa Longo Borghini just ahead of teammate Gaia Realini, the duo putting in a strong performance to finish 1-2 on the third stage to Jebel Hafeet. UAE Team ADQ’s Silvia Persico completed the overall podium in third. DSM-Firmenich’s Charlotte Kool bookended the race with two victories on the flat stages, but will not be on the start line this year due to illness.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/2024-pro-cycling-cyclocross-world-championships\">Pro Log: British Cycling to organise Tour of Britain races, Cyclocross Worlds, Will Barta earns first pro win</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/red-bull-bora-hansgrohe\">What does Red Bull’s takeover of Bora-Hansgrohe mean for cycling?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/elisa-longo-borghini-cyclist\">‘I hate racing for second’: Elisa Longo Borghini profile</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/omloop-het-nieuwsblad-guide\">Omloop Het Nieuwsblad 2024: Routes, TV and everything you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>UAE Tour Women 2024: Key information</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Elisa-Longo-Borghini-and-Gaia-Realini-at-UAE-Tour-Women-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Elisa-Longo-Borghini-and-Gaia-Realini-at-UAE-Tour-Women-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Elisa-Longo-Borghini-and-Gaia-Realini-at-UAE-Tour-Women-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Elisa-Longo-Borghini-and-Gaia-Realini-at-UAE-Tour-Women-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Elisa-Longo-Borghini-and-Gaia-Realini-at-UAE-Tour-Women-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Elisa-Longo-Borghini-and-Gaia-Realini-at-UAE-Tour-Women-2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Elisa-Longo-Borghini-and-Gaia-Realini-at-UAE-Tour-Women-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Elisa-Longo-Borghini-and-Gaia-Realini-at-UAE-Tour-Women-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Elisa-Longo-Borghini-and-Gaia-Realini-at-UAE-Tour-Women-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Elisa-Longo-Borghini-and-Gaia-Realini-at-UAE-Tour-Women-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Elisa-Longo-Borghini-and-Gaia-Realini-at-UAE-Tour-Women-350x233.jpeg 350w\" /><figcaption>Giro d'Italia</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Date:</strong> 8th-11th February 2024<br /><strong>Start: </strong>Dubai<br /><strong>Finish: </strong>Abu Dhabi<br /><strong>Stages: </strong>4<br /><strong>Distance:</strong> 468km<br /><strong>2023 winner: </strong>Elisa Longo Borghini (Lidl-Trek)<br /><strong>UK television coverage:</strong> Discovery+, Eurosport</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>UAE Tour Women 2024: The route</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The UAE Tour Women 2024 has a similar parcours to last year. Two flatter stages for the sprinters or an ambitious breakaway precede a day for the climbers on Stage 3 to Jebel Hafeet, closing out with another flatter sprint stage for the final day.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1, Thursday 8th February: Dubai – Dubai, 122km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.45.13-970x480.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.45.13-970x480.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.45.13-300x149.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.45.13-768x380.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.45.13-1536x761.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.45.13-2048x1014.png 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.45.13-750x371.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.45.13-1140x565.png 1140w\" /><figcaption>First Cycling</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The UAE Tour Women 2024 begins with a pan flat stage around Dubai. The peloton heads out towards a sprint point at Flamingo Lake before turning back on themselves and riding to the finish line at Dubai Harbour.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2, Friday 9th February: Al Mirfa – Madinat Zayed, 113km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"479\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.46.14-970x479.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.46.14-970x479.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.46.14-300x148.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.46.14-768x379.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.46.14-1536x759.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.46.14-2048x1011.png 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.46.14-750x370.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.46.14-1140x563.png 1140w\" /><figcaption>First Cycling</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Another flat day awaits the peloton from Al Mirfa to Madinat Zayed, crossing over 60km of desert. The final 10km are on a wide, straight road.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3, Saturday 10th February: Al Ain – Jebel Hafeet, 128km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"479\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.47.14-970x479.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.47.14-970x479.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.47.14-300x148.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.47.14-768x379.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.47.14-1536x758.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.47.14-2048x1011.png 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.47.14-750x370.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.47.14-1140x563.png 1140w\" /><figcaption>First Cycling</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Ah, some elevation. The final climb of Jebel Hafeet stands at 10.8km in length and peaks with a maximum gradient of 11% coming 3km from the finish.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4, Sunday 11th February: Abu Dhabi – Abu Dhabi, 105km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"479\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.48.06-970x479.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.48.06-970x479.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.48.06-300x148.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.48.06-768x380.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.48.06-1536x759.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.48.06-2048x1012.png 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.48.06-750x371.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-07-at-11.48.06-1140x563.png 1140w\" /><figcaption>First Cycling</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Back to the flat. The final stage of the UAE Tour Women 2024 heads in the direction of the Yas Marina Circuit for an intermediate sprint, a place that also hosts the Abu Dhabi Grand Prix if you’re into Formula 1.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>From there, riders will race towards the Sorbonne University before finishing at Abu Dhabi Breakwater where the race’s victor will be crowned.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>UAE Tour Women 2024: How to watch</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We’re still mourning the loss of GCN+, but the UAE Tour Women 2024 will be available to watch in the UK on <a href=\"https://auth.discoveryplus.com/gb/product?flow=purchase&amp;videoAssetId=6021174\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> for £6.99 per month with the basic package, which includes cycling and all other Eurosport programmes. It will also be shown on the TV channel Eurosport 2 in the UK.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while travelling abroad in countries without access.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find way to watch cycling without having to pay for broadcasters services, and costs £5.36 per month, with three months free. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">How to watch cycling post-GCN+</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1, Thursday 8th February</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>10:30 – 13:00<br /><strong>Eurosport 2: </strong>11:50 – 13:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2, Friday 9th February</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>10:30 – 13:00<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 11:50 – 13:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3, Saturday 10th February</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>10:30 – 13:00<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 11:50 – 13:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4, Sunday 11th February</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>10:30 – 13:00<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 11:50 – 13:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>UAE Tour Women 2024: Start list</h2>\n\n\n\n<div><p><em>Data powered by <a href=\"https://firstcycling.com/race.php?r=18130&amp;y=2024&amp;k=8\" target=\"_blank\">FirstCycling.com</a></em></p></div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/uae-tour-women-preview\">UAE Tour Women 2024: Route, TV and everything you need to know</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Robyn Davidson &#124; Editorial Assistant","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"277200b51a8dc87733fe0138e55ac8012376589db86618484ce9224c77a44bb1","category":"Cycling"}